definitions.definition: A left tributary of Rhine , flowing through the departments of Vosges , Meurthe-et-Moselle and Moselle in northeastern France , through Luxembourg , and through the states of Rhineland-Palatinate and Saarland , Germany .
A department of Grand Est , France .

definitions.definition: A light white wine , made from Riesling grapes originating in the valley of this river.
